<ab><lb n="1"/><w lemma="θεά">θεὰν</w>  <persName type="divine"><name>Ἀφροδεί<lb n="1a" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></name></persName>  <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Goddess Aphrodi<supplied reason="lost">te</supplied>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>A staue of the goddess must have stood above: the name of the donor/dedicator no doubt followed. It would obviously be likely that the main civic deity should be honoured in the Bouleuterion, but it is hardly less appropriate in an Odeon.</p>
         </div>
